  "output": "## Test Coverage Analysis — jobsquare\n\n**Current state: 0% coverage.** No `tests/` directory, no pytest config, no `conftest.py`, no test dependencies in `requirements.txt`, no test step in `.github/workflows/scrape.yaml`. Every module below (`models.py`, `filters.py`, `store.py`, `notify.py`, `fetchers.py`, `pipeline.py`, `cli.py`, `agent.py`) is completely unexercised.\n\n### Recommended setup (needed before any skeleton below runs)\n\n```\n# requirements-dev.txt\npytest>=8.0\npytest-asyncio>=0.24\n```\n\nhttpx ships `httpx.MockTransport`, so no extra HTTP-mocking dependency is required for `fetchers.py`.\n\n```python\n# conftest.py\nimport pytest\nfrom store import Store\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef store(tmp_path):\n    with Store(tmp_path / \"jobs.db\") as s:\n        yield s\n```\n\n---\n\n## 1. `models.py`\n\n**Untested:** `parse_posted_at`, `Job.key`, `Job.posted_dt`, `Job.content_hash`, `Job.to_row`.\n\n**Edge cases not covered:**\n- epoch seconds vs. epoch milliseconds boundary (the `>= 1e12` branch)\n- negative/garbage numeric strings (`\"-1\"`, `\"12abc\"`)\n- trailing `Z` normalization pre/post Python 3.11\n- empty string / `None`-like input → `None`\n- naive ISO datetime (no tzinfo) gets UTC attached\n- `content_hash` changes when `title`/`location`/`url`/`department` change but **not** when `posted_at`/`salary_range` change (this is a real invariant the dedup logic depends on)\n\n```python\n# tests/test_models.py\nimport pytest\nfrom datetime import timezone\nfrom models import Job, parse_posted_at\n\n@pytest.mark.parametrize(\"raw,expected_epoch\", [\n    (\"1643241332430\", 1643241332),      # Lever ms\n    (\"1643241332\", 1643241332),          # plain seconds\n    (\"2022-01-26T00:00:00Z\", 1643155200),\n])\ndef test_parse_posted_at_numeric_and_iso(raw, expected_epoch):\n    dt = parse_posted_at(raw)\n    assert dt.tzinfo == timezone.utc\n    assert int(dt.timestamp()) == expected_epoch\n\n@pytest.mark.parametrize(\"raw\", [\"\", None, \"Posted 3 Days Ago\", \"not-a-date\"])\ndef test_parse_posted_at_unparseable_returns_none(raw):\n    assert parse_posted_at(raw) is None\n\ndef test_parse_posted_at_naive_iso_gets_utc():\n    dt = parse_posted_at(\"2022-01-26T00:00:00\")\n    assert dt.tzinfo == timezone.utc\n\ndef test_job_key_is_stable_identity():\n    j = Job(source=\"greenhouse\", company=\"acme\", external_id=\"42\", title=\"X\", url=\"u\")\n    assert j.key == \"greenhouse:acme:42\"\n\ndef test_content_hash_changes_on_material_fields_only():\n    base = dict(source=\"lever\", company=\"acme\", external_id=\"1\", title=\"Eng\", url=\"u\",\n                location=\"NYC\", department=\"Infra\")\n    j1 = Job(**base)\n    j2 = Job(**{**base, \"posted_at\": \"2024-01-01\", \"salary_range\": \"$1\"})\n    assert j1.content_hash == j2.content_hash   # non-material fields ignored\n\n    j3 = Job(**{**base, \"title\": \"Sr Eng\"})\n    assert j1.content_hash != j3.content_hash   # material field changes hash\n\ndef test_to_row_drops_raw_and_adds_key_and_hash():\n    j = Job(source=\"s\", company=\"c\", external_id=\"1\", title=\"t\", url=\"u\", raw={\"x\": 1})\n    row = j.to_row()\n    assert \"raw\" not in row\n    assert row[\"key\"] == j.key\n    assert row[\"content_hash\"] == j.content_hash\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. `filters.py`\n\n**Untested:** `_compile`, `match`, `filter_jobs`.\n\n**Edge cases not covered:**\n- word-boundary matching (must not match `\"engineering\"` as a substring of `\"engineer\"` vs. intended matches)\n- exclude takes priority over include\n- case-insensitivity\n- location substring matching (`\"NYC\"` vs. `\"New York, NYC\"`)\n- `cutoff` set but job has unparseable `posted_at` → **kept, not dropped** (explicit behavior in the docstring — worth locking in)\n- `max_age_days` absent vs. `0` vs. float days\n- regex special characters in keywords (e.g. `\"C++\"`) must not raise/misbehave via `re.escape`\n\n```python\n# tests/test_filters.py\nfrom datetime import datetime, timedelta, timezone\nfrom models import Job\nfrom filters import match, filter_jobs\n\ndef _job(**kw):\n    return Job(source=\"s\", company=\"c\", external_id=\"1\", title=\"Software Engineer\",\n               url=\"u\", location=\"Seattle, WA\", department=\"Infra\", **kw)\n\ndef test_match_word_boundary_not_substring():\n    j = _job(title=\"Sales Engineering Manager\")\n    assert match(j, include=[\"engineer\"]) is False  # \"engineering\" != \"engineer\"\n\ndef test_match_exclude_wins_over_include():\n    j = _job(title=\"Senior Software Engineer - Staff\")\n    assert match(j, include=[\"engineer\"], exclude=[\"staff\"]) is False\n\ndef test_match_case_insensitive():\n    j = _job(title=\"SOFTWARE ENGINEER\")\n    assert match(j, include=[\"software engineer\"]) is True\n\ndef test_match_location_substring():\n    j = _job(location=\"Remote - New York, NYC\")\n    assert match(j, locations=[\"nyc\"]) is True\n    assert match(j, locations=[\"Austin\"]) is False\n\ndef test_match_cutoff_keeps_unparseable_dates():\n    j = _job(posted_at=\"Posted 3 Days Ago\")\n    cutoff = datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=1)\n    assert match(j, cutoff=cutoff) is True  # can't confirm stale -> keep\n\ndef test_match_cutoff_drops_old_dated_job():\n    old = (datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=10)).isoformat()\n    j = _job(posted_at=old)\n    cutoff = datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=1)\n    assert match(j, cutoff=cutoff) is False\n\ndef test_include_special_regex_chars_are_escaped():\n    j = _job(title=\"C++ Engineer\")\n    assert match(j, include=[\"C++\"]) is True  # would raise/misbehave without re.escape\n\ndef test_filter_jobs_applies_max_age_days():\n    fresh = _job(external_id=\"1\", posted_at=datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat())\n    stale = _job(external_id=\"2\",\n                 posted_at=(datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=30)).isoformat())\n    out = filter_jobs([fresh, stale], {\"max_age_days\": 7})\n    assert [j.external_id for j in out] == [\"1\"]\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. `store.py`\n\n**Untested:** entire class — schema creation, migration, `diff`, meta get/set, `next_seq`, `added_since`, `count`, context-manager protocol.\n\n**Edge cases / integration gaps:**\n- **migration path**: a pre-existing DB file *without* `salary_range` gets the column added on open (currently impossible to hit without hand-crafting an old schema)\n- `diff()` three branches: brand-new key, same `content_hash` (only `last_seen` bumped, `first_seen` untouched), changed `content_hash` (fields updated, both timestamps advance appropriately)\n- `next_seq` concurrency guarantee — this is explicitly called out as protecting **parallel pipeline workers** (see the `BEGIN IMMEDIATE` comment, and the known `jobsquare-parallel-worker-collisions` issue) but has zero concurrency test\n- `added_since` boundary: strictly `>` not `>=`\n- `set_meta` upsert overwrites existing key\n\n```python\n# tests/test_store.py\nimport threading\nfrom models import Job\nfrom store import Store\n\ndef _job(ext_id, title=\"Eng\"):\n    return Job(source=\"greenhouse\", company=\"acme\", external_id=ext_id,\n               title=title, url=\"u\", location=\"NYC\")\n\ndef test_migration_adds_salary_range_to_old_schema(tmp_path):\n    import sqlite3\n    path = tmp_path / \"old.db\"\n    conn = sqlite3.connect(path)\n    conn.executescript(\"\"\"\n        CREATE TABLE jobs (key TEXT PRIMARY KEY, source TEXT, company TEXT,\n            external_id TEXT, title TEXT, url TEXT, location TEXT, department TEXT,\n            employment_type TEXT, posted_at TEXT, content_hash TEXT,\n            first_seen TEXT, last_seen TEXT);\n        CREATE TABLE meta (k TEXT PRIMARY KEY, v TEXT);\n    \"\"\")\n    conn.close()\n    with Store(path) as s:\n        cols = {r[\"name\"] for r in s.conn.execute(\"PRAGMA table_info(jobs)\")}\n        assert \"salary_range\" in cols\n\ndef test_diff_new_job_inserted(store):\n    new, changed = store.diff([_job(\"1\")])\n    assert len(new) == 1 and not changed\n    assert store.count() == 1\n\ndef test_diff_unchanged_job_only_bumps_last_seen(store):\n    store.diff([_job(\"1\")])\n    row1 = store.conn.execute(\"SELECT first_seen, last_seen FROM jobs\").fetchone()\n    new, changed = store.diff([_job(\"1\")])\n    row2 = store.conn.execute(\"SELECT first_seen, last_seen FROM jobs\").fetchone()\n    assert not new and not changed\n    assert row1[\"first_seen\"] == row2[\"first_seen\"]\n\ndef test_diff_changed_content_marks_changed(store):\n    store.diff([_job(\"1\", title=\"Eng\")])\n    new, changed = store.diff([_job(\"1\", title=\"Sr Eng\")])\n    assert not new\n    assert [j.external_id for j in changed] == [\"1\"]\n\ndef test_added_since_is_strictly_after(store):\n    store.diff([_job(\"1\")])\n    ts_before = store.get_meta(\"nonexistent\") or \"1970-01-01T00:00:00+00:00\"\n    rows = store.added_since(ts_before)\n    assert len(rows) == 1\n    exact_ts = rows[0][\"first_seen\"]\n    assert store.added_since(exact_ts) == []  # boundary is exclusive\n\ndef test_set_meta_upserts(store):\n    store.set_meta(\"k\", \"v1\")\n    store.set_meta(\"k\", \"v2\")\n    assert store.get_meta(\"k\") == \"v2\"\n\ndef test_next_seq_increments(store):\n    assert store.next_seq(\"counter\") == 1\n    assert store.next_seq(\"counter\") == 2\n\ndef test_next_seq_serializes_concurrent_callers(tmp_path):\n    # Regression guard for the parallel-worker collision failure mode.\n    results = []\n    def worker():\n        with Store(tmp_path / \"shared.db\") as s:\n            results.append(s.next_seq(\"report_seq\"))\n    threads = [threading.Thread(target=worker) for _ in range(10)]\n    [t.start() for t in threads]\n    [t.join() for t in threads]\n    assert sorted(results) == list(range(1, 11))  # no duplicate/skipped ids\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. `notify.py`\n\n**Untested:** every notifier and `dispatch`.\n\n**Critical gap:** `dispatch()`'s exception isolation (`notify_sms` calling `raise_for_status()`) is the one piece of behavior explicitly designed to fail safely — it has no test proving a failing notifier doesn't take down the others.\n\n**Edge cases:**\n- each notifier no-ops when its env var(s) are unset, and no-ops when `new`/`changed` are both empty (avoid sending an empty Slack/email/SMS ping)\n- `notify_sms` truncation (`_sms_body` limit + \"+N more\" line) and ASCII-only body\n- `notify_email` missing `SMTP_USER` skips `.login()`\n\n```python\n# tests/test_notify.py\nimport pytest\nimport notify\nfrom models import Job\n\ndef _job(i):\n    return Job(source=\"s\", company=\"c\", external_id=str(i), title=f\"Job {i}\", url=\"u\")\n\ndef test_notify_slack_noop_without_webhook_env(monkeypatch):\n    monkeypatch.delenv(\"SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL\", raising=False)\n    called = []\n    monkeypatch.setattr(\"httpx.post\", lambda *a, **k: called.append(1))\n    notify.notify_slack([_job(1)], [])\n    assert not called\n\ndef test_notify_slack_noop_when_nothing_new(monkeypatch):\n    monkeypatch.setenv(\"SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL\", \"https://hooks/x\")\n    called = []\n    monkeypatch.setattr(\"httpx.post\", lambda *a, **k: called.append(1))\n    notify.notify_slack([], [])\n    assert not called\n\ndef test_sms_body_truncates_and_is_ascii():\n    jobs = [_job(i) for i in range(12)]\n    body = notify._sms_body(jobs, [], limit=8)\n    assert \"+4 more\" in body\n    assert body.isascii()\n\ndef test_dispatch_isolates_failing_notifier(monkeypatch, capsys):\n    def boom(new, changed):\n        raise RuntimeError(\"twilio 400\")\n    monkeypatch.setattr(notify, \"NOTIFIERS\",\n                         [notify.notify_console, boom, notify.notify_console])\n    notify.dispatch([_job(1)], [])  # must not raise\n    out = capsys.readouterr().out\n    assert \"notifier boom failed\" in out\n    assert out.count(\"1 NEW listing(s)\") == 2  # both console calls still ran\n\ndef test_notify_sms_missing_env_is_noop(monkeypatch):\n    for v in (\"TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID\", \"TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN\", \"TWILIO_FROM\", \"TWILIO_TO\"):\n        monkeypatch.delenv(v, raising=False)\n    called = []\n    monkeypatch.setattr(\"httpx.post\", lambda *a, **k: called.append(1))\n    notify.notify_sms([_job(1)], [])\n    assert not called\n\ndef test_notify_sms_raises_on_http_error(monkeypatch):\n    monkeypatch.setenv(\"TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID\", \"sid\")\n    monkeypatch.setenv(\"TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN\", \"tok\")\n    monkeypatch.setenv(\"TWILIO_FROM\", \"+1\")\n    monkeypatch.setenv(\"TWILIO_TO\", \"+2\")\n    class FakeResp:\n        def raise_for_status(self): raise RuntimeError(\"bad creds\")\n    monkeypatch.setattr(\"httpx.post\", lambda *a, **k: FakeResp())\n    with pytest.raises(RuntimeError):\n        notify.notify_sms([_job(1)], [])\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. `fetchers.py` (1146 lines, the largest surface — currently **0 tests**)\n\nThis file is the highest-risk gap: ~20 bespoke ATS parsers, most reverse-engineered from undocumented HTML/JSON blobs, each with brittle assumptions the memory files already flag as fragile (Meta's rotating `doc_id`, Apple's nanosecond timestamps, ByteDance's strict body schema). Parser functions are pure (`payload -> list[Job]`) and are cheap to unit test with fixture payloads; fetch functions need `httpx.MockTransport`.\n\n**Untested infrastructure:**\n- `_request` retry/backoff (retryable status codes, exhaustion → `RuntimeError`, non-retryable raises immediately, `TransportError` retried)\n- `_balanced_json` (nested braces, braces inside strings, escaped quotes, unterminated input)\n- `fetch_all` (concurrency cap via semaphore, per-source failure isolation + logging, doesn't close a caller-supplied client)\n- `fetch_source` unknown ATS → `ValueError`\n\n**Untested parsers (representative pattern, applies uniformly across all 20):**\n- missing/None optional fields don't crash (`greenhouse` job with no `departments`, `lever` job with no `categories`)\n- pagination loop termination: stops on first page with no *new* IDs (not just empty page) — this matters for `twosigma`'s \"each role renders 3x\" case and `google`'s stale-page case\n- dedup-by-`external_id` across pages actually dedups\n- safety caps (`max_pages`, Workday's `offset > 5000`) are honored\n\n**Untested bespoke logic:**\n- `_ds1_posted_at` / `_apple_posted_at` / `_amazon_posted_at` — date-normalization edge cases per source format\n- `_bd_location` parent-chain walk with missing/partial `city_info`\n- `fetch_ashby` 200 vs 404-fallback vs other-status-raises branches\n- `fetch_meta`'s `\"for (;;);\"` prefix stripping and GraphQL `errors` → `RuntimeError`\n- `_apple_hydration` malformed JSON → `None`\n\n```python\n# tests/test_fetchers_parsers.py\nfrom fetchers import (parse_greenhouse, parse_lever, _lever_salary, parse_ashby,\n                       _bd_location, _amazon_posted_at, _apple_posted_at,\n                       _balanced_json, parse_meta, _extract_ds1)\n\ndef test_parse_greenhouse_missing_optional_fields():\n    data = {\"jobs\": [{\"id\": 1, \"title\": \"Eng\"}]}  # no location/departments/updated_at\n    jobs = parse_greenhouse(\"acme\", data)\n    assert jobs[0].location == \"\" and jobs[0].department == \"\"\n\ndef test_lever_salary_prefers_min_max_over_description():\n    j = {\"salaryRange\": {\"min\": 100000, \"max\": 150000, \"currency\": \"USD\"},\n         \"salaryDescriptionPlain\": \"fallback\"}\n    assert _lever_salary(j) == \"USD 100,000–150,000\"\n\ndef test_lever_salary_falls_back_to_description():\n    j = {\"salaryDescriptionPlain\": \"Competitive\"}\n    assert _lever_salary(j) == \"Competitive\"\n\ndef test_parse_ashby_skips_unlisted():\n    data = {\"jobs\": [{\"id\": \"1\", \"isListed\": False}, {\"id\": \"2\", \"title\": \"Eng\"}]}\n    out = parse_ashby(\"co\", data)\n    assert [j.external_id for j in out] == [\"2\"]\n\ndef test_bd_location_walks_parent_chain():\n    city = {\"en_name\": \"Austin\", \"parent\": {\"en_name\": \"Texas\",\n             \"parent\": {\"en_name\": \"USA\", \"parent\": None}}}\n    assert _bd_location(city) == \"Austin, Texas, USA\"\n\ndef test_bd_location_none_returns_empty():\n    assert _bd_location(None) == \"\"\n\ndef test_amazon_posted_at_parses_and_handles_garbage():\n    assert _amazon_posted_at(\"June 26, 2026\") == \"2026-06-26T00:00:00+00:00\"\n    assert _amazon_posted_at(\"\") == \"\"\n    assert _amazon_posted_at(\"garbage\") == \"\"\n\ndef test_apple_posted_at_truncates_nanoseconds():\n    out = _apple_posted_at(\"2024-01-01T00:00:03.812668311Z\")\n    assert out == \"2024-01-01T00:00:03.812668+00:00\"\n\ndef test_balanced_json_handles_braces_inside_strings():\n    text = '{\"a\": \"} not a close {\", \"b\": 1}TRAILING'\n    assert _balanced_json(text, 0) == '{\"a\": \"} not a close {\", \"b\": 1}'\n\ndef test_balanced_json_unterminated_returns_none():\n    assert _balanced_json('{\"a\": 1', 0) is None\n\ndef test_parse_meta_dedups_and_skips_falsy_id():\n    results = [{\"id\": \"1\", \"title\": \"A\"}, {\"id\": \"1\", \"title\": \"A dup\"}, {\"id\": None}]\n    out = parse_meta(\"meta\", results)\n    assert [j.external_id for j in out] == [\"1\"]\n\ndef test_extract_ds1_fallback_regex_when_sidechannel_missing():\n    html = \"AF_initDataCallback({key: 'ds:1', data:[[{\\\"x\\\":1}]]});\"\n    # primary regex expects \", sideChannel\" — must hit fallback branch\n    assert _extract_ds1(html) == [{\"x\": 1}]\n```\n\n```python\n# tests/test_fetchers_http.py\nimport httpx\nimport pytest\nfrom fetchers import _request, fetch_all, fetch_source\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_request_retries_then_succeeds(monkeypatch):\n    monkeypatch.setattr(\"asyncio.sleep\", lambda *_: None)  # skip real backoff\n    calls = {\"n\": 0}\n    def handler(request):\n        calls[\"n\"] += 1\n        if calls[\"n\"] < 3:\n            return httpx.Response(503)\n        return httpx.Response(200, json={\"ok\": True})\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient(transport=httpx.MockTransport(handler)) as c:\n        r = await _request(c, \"https://x/test\")\n    assert r.json() == {\"ok\": True}\n    assert calls[\"n\"] == 3\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_request_exhausts_retries_raises_runtimeerror(monkeypatch):\n    monkeypatch.setattr(\"asyncio.sleep\", lambda *_: None)\n    handler = lambda request: httpx.Response(500)\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient(transport=httpx.MockTransport(handler)) as c:\n        with pytest.raises(RuntimeError, match=\"failed to fetch\"):\n            await _request(c, \"https://x/test\", retries=2)\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_request_non_retryable_status_raises_immediately():\n    calls = {\"n\": 0}\n    def handler(request):\n        calls[\"n\"] += 1\n        return httpx.Response(404)\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient(transport=httpx.MockTransport(handler)) as c:\n        with pytest.raises(RuntimeError):\n            await _request(c, \"https://x/test\", retries=4)\n    assert calls[\"n\"] == 1  # no retry on non-retryable status\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_fetch_source_unknown_ats_raises():\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient() as c:\n        with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"unknown ATS\"):\n            await fetch_source(c, {\"ats\": \"bogus\", \"company\": \"x\"})\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_fetch_all_isolates_per_source_failures(capsys):\n    def handler(request):\n        if \"boards-api.greenhouse.io\" in str(request.url):\n            return httpx.Response(500)\n        return httpx.Response(200, json={\"jobs\": [{\"id\": 1, \"title\": \"Eng\"}]})\n    client = httpx.AsyncClient(transport=httpx.MockTransport(handler))\n    sources = [{\"ats\": \"greenhouse\", \"company\": \"bad\"},\n               {\"ats\": \"greenhouse\", \"company\": \"good\"}]\n    # good source uses same mocked host, so isolate via a company-based handler instead\n    # in practice: two different ats/companies pointed at distinct mock responses\n    jobs = await fetch_all(sources, client=client)\n    await client.aclose()\n    assert \"failed\" in capsys.readouterr().out\n```\n\n*(The pagination-termination pattern — `twosigma`, `optiver`, `apple`, `eightfold`, `bytedance`, `phenom`, `microsoft`, `netflix`, `amazon`, `google` — repeats across ~10 fetchers; one parametrized test per fetcher against a `MockTransport` returning 2 pages then an empty/repeat page is the minimum bar.)*\n\n---\n\n## 6. `pipeline.py`\n\n**Untested:** `load_config` defaults, `run()` (dry-run vs. persisted path), `run_sync`.\n\n```python\n# tests/test_pipeline.py\nimport pytest\nfrom unittest.mock import AsyncMock\nimport pipeline\nfrom models import Job\n\ndef test_load_config_fills_defaults(tmp_path):\n    cfg_path = tmp_path / \"sources.yaml\"\n    cfg_path.write_text(\"sources: []\\n\")\n    cfg = pipeline.load_config(cfg_path)\n    assert cfg[\"db\"] == \"jobs.db\" and cfg[\"concurrency\"] == 8 and cfg[\"filters\"] == {}\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_run_dry_run_does_not_persist(tmp_path, monkeypatch):\n    cfg_path = tmp_path / \"sources.yaml\"\n    cfg_path.write_text(f\"sources: []\\ndb: {tmp_path / 'jobs.db'}\\n\")\n    monkeypatch.setattr(pipeline, \"fetch_all\",\n                         AsyncMock(return_value=[Job(source=\"s\", company=\"c\",\n                                   external_id=\"1\", title=\"Eng\", url=\"u\")]))\n    result = await pipeline.run(cfg_path, dry_run=True)\n    assert result == {\"matched\": 1, \"new\": 0, \"changed\": 0}\n    assert not (tmp_path / \"jobs.db\").exists()\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_run_persists_and_dispatches(tmp_path, monkeypatch):\n    cfg_path = tmp_path / \"sources.yaml\"\n    db_path = tmp_path / \"jobs.db\"\n    cfg_path.write_text(f\"sources: []\\ndb: {db_path}\\n\")\n    job = Job(source=\"s\", company=\"c\", external_id=\"1\", title=\"Eng\", url=\"u\")\n    monkeypatch.setattr(pipeline, \"fetch_all\", AsyncMock(return_value=[job]))\n    dispatched = {}\n    monkeypatch.setattr(pipeline, \"dispatch\",\n                         lambda new, changed: dispatched.update(new=new, changed=changed))\n    result = await pipeline.run(cfg_path, dry_run=False)\n    assert result == {\"matched\": 1, \"new\": 1, \"changed\": 0}\n    assert dispatched[\"new\"] == [job]\n    assert db_path.exists()\n```\n\n---\n\n## 7. `cli.py`\n\n**Untested:** argument wiring only (thin, but currently zero-coverage).\n\n```python\n# tests/test_cli.py\nfrom unittest.mock import patch\nimport cli\n\ndef test_main_passes_config_and_dry_run(monkeypatch):\n    with patch(\"cli.run_sync\") as mock_run:\n        monkeypatch.setattr(\"sys.argv\", [\"cli.py\", \"-c\", \"custom.yaml\", \"--dry-run\"])\n        cli.main()\n    mock_run.assert_called_once_with(\"custom.yaml\", dry_run=True)\n\ndef test_main_defaults_config():\n    with patch(\"cli.run_sync\") as mock_run:\n        with patch(\"sys.argv\", [\"cli.py\"]):\n            cli.main()\n    mock_run.assert_called_once_with(\"sources.yaml\", dry_run=False)\n```\n\n---\n\n## 8. `agent.py`\n\n**Untested:** every `cmd_*` handler, `_normalize_ats`, `_chrome_bin`, `run_claude`, `main`'s arg-routing.\n\n**High-value edge cases:**\n- `cmd_db_new`: first-run window (no marker) vs. marker-based `since`; `--posted-days` + `--dated-only` interaction (`dropped_old`/`undated_kept`/`undated_dropped` counters); truncation happens at a `first_seen` **group boundary**, never mid-group (this is a documented invariant — a naive `rows[:limit]` slice would violate it)\n- `cmd_db_mark`: `--now` vs. explicit watermark vs. invalid ISO string (exit 2) vs. neither passed (exit 2)\n- `_normalize_ats`: replacements skip `<style>`/`<script>` blocks and tag attributes, only touch text nodes; counts aggregate correctly\n- `cmd_pdf_render`: missing input file → exit 2; PDF magic-byte validation failure path\n- `main()`: mode-word vs. `-i`/flag boundary detection (`words[:i]` split) routes correctly for `python agent.py apply --dry-run`-style invocations\n\n```python\n# tests/test_agent.py\nimport json\nfrom datetime import datetime, timedelta, timezone\nimport pytest\nfrom agent import cmd_db_new, cmd_db_mark, _normalize_ats\nfrom models import Job\nfrom store import Store\n\ndef test_db_new_first_run_uses_since_days_window(tmp_path, capsys):\n    cfg = tmp_path / \"sources.yaml\"\n    db = tmp_path / \"jobs.db\"\n    cfg.write_text(f\"sources: []\\ndb: {db}\\n\")\n    with Store(db) as s:\n        s.diff([Job(source=\"s\", company=\"c\", external_id=\"1\", title=\"Eng\", url=\"u\")])\n    cmd_db_new([\"-c\", str(cfg), \"--since-days\", \"7\"])\n    out = json.loads(capsys.readouterr().out)\n    assert out[\"first_run\"] is True and out[\"count\"] == 1\n\ndef test_db_new_truncates_at_group_boundary_not_mid_group(tmp_path, capsys, monkeypatch):\n    cfg = tmp_path / \"sources.yaml\"\n    db = tmp_path / \"jobs.db\"\n    cfg.write_text(f\"sources: []\\ndb: {db}\\n\")\n    with Store(db) as s:\n        # two separate pipeline runs -> two distinct first_seen groups of 3 each\n        s.diff([Job(source=\"s\", company=\"c\", external_id=str(i), title=\"E\", url=\"u\")\n                for i in range(3)])\n        s.diff([Job(source=\"s\", company=\"c\", external_id=str(i), title=\"E\", url=\"u\")\n                for i in range(3, 6)])\n    cmd_db_new([\"-c\", str(cfg), \"--limit\", \"4\"])  # limit falls mid-second-group\n    out = json.loads(capsys.readouterr().out)\n    assert out[\"count\"] == 3 and out[\"truncated\"] is True  # only first group kept whole\n\ndef test_db_mark_rejects_invalid_watermark(tmp_path, capsys):\n    cfg = tmp_path / \"sources.yaml\"\n    cfg.write_text(f\"sources: []\\ndb: {tmp_path / 'jobs.db'}\\n\")\n    rc = cmd_db_mark([\"not-a-timestamp\", \"-c\", str(cfg)])\n    assert rc == 2\n\ndef test_db_mark_requires_watermark_or_now(tmp_path):\n    cfg = tmp_path / \"sources.yaml\"\n    cfg.write_text(f\"sources: []\\ndb: {tmp_path / 'jobs.db'}\\n\")\n    assert cmd_db_mark([\"-c\", str(cfg)]) == 2\n\ndef test_normalize_ats_skips_style_and_script_blocks():\n    html = '<style>content: \"\\u2014\";</style><p>real \\u2014 dash</p><script>\"\\u2014\"</script>'\n    out, counts = _normalize_ats(html)\n    assert '<style>content: \"\\u2014\"' in out          # untouched inside <style>\n    assert \"real - dash\" in out                        # replaced in body text\n    assert counts[\"em-dash\"] == 1                       # only the body occurrence counted\n\ndef test_normalize_ats_does_not_touch_tag_attributes():\n    html = '<a href=\"x\\u2014y\">text\\u2014here</a>'\n    out, _ = _normalize_ats(html)\n    assert 'href=\"x\\u2014y\"' in out       # attribute left alone\n    assert \"text-here\" in out             # text node replaced\n```\n\n---\n\n## Integration test gaps (no coverage exists at any level)\n\n1. **End-to-end pipeline run**: config → `fetch_all` (mocked transport) → `filter_jobs` → `Store.diff` → `notify.dispatch`, asserting DB state and notifier calls together — currently every layer is tested (if at all) in isolation.\n2. **Scan → mark → rescan cycle**: `agent.py db-new` followed by `db-mark <watermark>` followed by another `db-new` must not re-surface already-marked rows, and must correctly resume from the watermark rather than `--now` (the docstring explicitly warns against using `--now` for this reason — no test locks in why).\n3. **Concurrent pipeline workers against one `jobs.db`**: your memory notes a *known* issue — `jobsquare-parallel-worker-collisions` (shared scratchpad paths + colliding report filenames corrupt concurrent runs). `Store.next_seq`'s `BEGIN IMMEDIATE` is the fix for the report-id half of that; there's no regression test proving it holds under real thread/process concurrency (skeleton above is a start, but a multi-process version closer to the real failure mode would be stronger).\n4. **`fetch_all` against a config with a real mix of ATS types**: verifies `fetch_source`'s registry dispatch end-to-end rather than each fetcher only ever being called directly in a unit test.\n5. **`sources.yaml` schema validation**: nothing validates that entries in the checked-in `sources.yaml` actually carry the required keys per ATS (`host`/`tenant`/`site` for Workday, `host`/`domain` for Eightfold, etc.) — a config typo currently only fails at 3am during the scheduled run.\n",
