        "content": "\nThis file is the highest-risk gap: ~20 bespoke ATS parsers, most reverse-engineered from undocumented HTML/JSON blobs, each with brittle assumptions the memory files already flag as fragile (Meta's rotating `doc_id`, Apple's nanosecond timestamps, ByteDance's strict body schema). Parser functions are pure (`payload -> list[Job]`) and are cheap to unit test with fixture payloads; fetch functions need `httpx.MockTransport`.\n\n**Untested infrastructure:**\n- `_request` retry/backoff (retryable status codes, exhaustion → `RuntimeError`, non-retryable raises immediately, `TransportError` retried)\n- `_balanced_json` (nested braces, braces inside strings, escaped quotes, unterminated input)\n- `fetch_all` (concurrency cap via semaphore, per-source failure isolation + logging, doesn't close a caller-supplied client)\n- `fetch_source` unknown ATS → `ValueError`\n\n**Untested parsers (representative pattern, applies uniformly across all 20):**\n- missing/None optional fields don't crash (`greenhouse` job with no `departments`, `lever` job with no `categories`)\n- pagination loop termination: stops on first page with no *new* IDs (not just empty page) — this matters for `twosigma`'s \"each role renders 3x\" case and `google`'s stale-page case\n- dedup-by-`external_id` across pages actually dedups\n- safety caps (`max_pages`, Workday's `offset > 5000`) are honored\n\n**Untested bespoke logic:**\n- `_ds1_posted_at` / `_apple_posted_at` / `_amazon_posted_at` — date-normalization edge cases per source format\n- `_bd_location` parent-chain walk with missing/partial `city_info`\n- `fetch_ashby` 200 vs 404-fallback vs other-status-raises branches\n- `fetch_meta`'s `\"for (;;);\"` prefix stripping and GraphQL `errors` → `RuntimeError`\n- `_apple_hydration` malformed JSON → `None`\n\n```python\n",
        "level": 2
      },
      {
        "title": "tests/test_fetchers_parsers.py",
        "content": "from fetchers import (parse_greenhouse, parse_lever, _lever_salary, parse_ashby,\n                       _bd_location, _amazon_posted_at, _apple_posted_at,\n                       _balanced_json, parse_meta, _extract_ds1)\n\ndef test_parse_greenhouse_missing_optional_fields():\n    data = {\"jobs\": [{\"id\": 1, \"title\": \"Eng\"}]}  # no location/departments/updated_at\n    jobs = parse_greenhouse(\"acme\", data)\n    assert jobs[0].location == \"\" and jobs[0].department == \"\"\n\ndef test_lever_salary_prefers_min_max_over_description():\n    j = {\"salaryRange\": {\"min\": 100000, \"max\": 150000, \"currency\": \"USD\"},\n         \"salaryDescriptionPlain\": \"fallback\"}\n    assert _lever_salary(j) == \"USD 100,000–150,000\"\n\ndef test_lever_salary_falls_back_to_description():\n    j = {\"salaryDescriptionPlain\": \"Competitive\"}\n    assert _lever_salary(j) == \"Competitive\"\n\ndef test_parse_ashby_skips_unlisted():\n    data = {\"jobs\": [{\"id\": \"1\", \"isListed\": False}, {\"id\": \"2\", \"title\": \"Eng\"}]}\n    out = parse_ashby(\"co\", data)\n    assert [j.external_id for j in out] == [\"2\"]\n\ndef test_bd_location_walks_parent_chain():\n    city = {\"en_name\": \"Austin\", \"parent\": {\"en_name\": \"Texas\",\n             \"parent\": {\"en_name\": \"USA\", \"parent\": None}}}\n    assert _bd_location(city) == \"Austin, Texas, USA\"\n\ndef test_bd_location_none_returns_empty():\n    assert _bd_location(None) == \"\"\n\ndef test_amazon_posted_at_parses_and_handles_garbage():\n    assert _amazon_posted_at(\"June 26, 2026\") == \"2026-06-26T00:00:00+00:00\"\n    assert _amazon_posted_at(\"\") == \"\"\n    assert _amazon_posted_at(\"garbage\") == \"\"\n\ndef test_apple_posted_at_truncates_nanoseconds():\n    out = _apple_posted_at(\"2024-01-01T00:00:03.812668311Z\")\n    assert out == \"2024-01-01T00:00:03.812668+00:00\"\n\ndef test_balanced_json_handles_braces_inside_strings():\n    text = '{\"a\": \"} not a close {\", \"b\": 1}TRAILING'\n    assert _balanced_json(text, 0) == '{\"a\": \"} not a close {\", \"b\": 1}'\n\ndef test_balanced_json_unterminated_returns_none():\n    assert _balanced_json('{\"a\": 1', 0) is None\n\ndef test_parse_meta_dedups_and_skips_falsy_id():\n    results = [{\"id\": \"1\", \"title\": \"A\"}, {\"id\": \"1\", \"title\": \"A dup\"}, {\"id\": None}]\n    out = parse_meta(\"meta\", results)\n    assert [j.external_id for j in out] == [\"1\"]\n\ndef test_extract_ds1_fallback_regex_when_sidechannel_missing():\n    html = \"AF_initDataCallback({key: 'ds:1', data:[[{\\\"x\\\":1}]]});\"\n    # primary regex expects \", sideChannel\" — must hit fallback branch\n    assert _extract_ds1(html) == [{\"x\": 1}]\n```\n\n```python\n",
